[Mohmmad Reza Hassani](http://mohammadrezahassani.com/) is an Iranian
professional photographer and photo-blogger who has lived and worked in
Lebanon since 2009 . His photo blog has become a source to discover Iran-
related affairs in Lebanon, from President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad's recent visit,
to the exhibitions and concerts of Iranian musicians.

**Waiting for Mahmoud**

In October, Mahmoud Ahmadinejad made a trip to Lebanon that [highlighted
Iranian sway](http://www.reuters.com/article/idUSTRE69A1KC20101011) in
Lebanon.

![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/12/ahmadinejad2.jpg)

![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/12/ahmadinejad1.jpg)

**Listening to a golden voice**

In August 2010, [Mohammad Reza
Shajarian](http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=130047062),
Iran's most famous protest singer
[performed](http://www.flickr.com/photos/l2eza/sets/72157624674812386/) a
concert in “Beit al dine” in Lebanon.

![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/shajarian.jpg)

**Colourful life**

The Iranian photo-blogger's camera does not only see celebrities, but life in
motion too.

![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/fishing.jpg)

